## Hypothesis

H0: Users don’t have a better overview of their pantry inventory with the app.

H1: Users have a better overview of their pantry inventory with the app.

## Effectiveness

Does barcode scanning help users determine whether a product is safe to consume given their preferences/allergies?

DV: Correct consumption decision (Safe / Unsafe / Not sure)

IV: barcode scanner vs manual lookup

## Efficiency

Does color-coding reduce the effort required to identify expired items?

DV: Perceived effort when identifying expired items

IV: Color-coded vs not color-coded expiry dates

Does the filter page reduce the effort required to identify items that expire today?

DV: Perceived effort when identifying expiring items

IV: Page (Homepage vs Filter page)

Does the safety badge presented make it easier to understand whether an item is safe?

DV: Perceived clarity / ease of understanding

IV: Safety badge vs manual lookup

## Satisfaction

How easy was it to add an item to an inventory?

DV: Perceived ease of adding an item

How easy was it to edit an item in an inventory?

DV: Perceived ease of editing an item

How easy was it to create a new inventory?

DV: Perceived ease of inventory creation

How easy was it to check if an item violated your preferences or contains allergies?

DV: Perceived ease of checking allergies / violations

